13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 2403. A. No person shall be eligible to participate in
15 the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program
16 unless the person:
17 1. Has complied with all of the rules promulgated by the
18 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education pursuant to the
19 provisions of the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars
20 Award Act, Section 2401 et seq. of this title, for the award,
21 regulation, and administration of scholarships; and
22 2. Qualifies as one of the following:
23 a. an Individual Applicant Qualified Student, which shall
24 mean a student who is a resident of the State of
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1282 Page 2
1 Oklahoma whose American College Testing Program score
2 or whose Scholastic Aptitude Test score falls within
3 the 99.5 to 100.0 percentile levels as administered in
4 the State of Oklahoma and whose grade point average
5 and/or class rank is exceptional, as determined by the
6 State Regents,
7 b. a Presidential Scholar, which shall mean a student
8 selected by the Commission on Presidential Scholars
9 administered by the United States Department of
10 Education,
11 c. a National Merit Scholar, which shall mean a student
12 designated as a National Merit Scholar by the National
13 Merit Scholarship Corporation,
14 d. a National Merit Finalist, which shall mean a student
15 designated as a National Merit Finalist by the
16 National Merit Scholarship Corporation, or
