2 awards, scholastic achievements, honors, and who
3 shows exceptional promise based on documentation
4 that may include, but not be limited to, teacher
5 recommendations, extracurricular activities, and
6 evidence of overcoming economic and social
7 obstacles as determined by the State Regents.
8 The State Regents shall ensure that standards of
9 high academic ability are documented.
10 Scholarship awards to Institutional Nominees
11 shall become effective when appropriate
12 documentation is verified by the State Regents.
