14 pursuant to the provisions of the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic
15 Rising Scholars Award Program unless the person is enrolled as a
16 full-time student at a public or private accredited institution of
17 higher education in Oklahoma.
18 C. The For a student who qualifies pursuant to subparagraphs a
19 through d of paragraph 2 of subsection A of this section and subject
20 to the availability of funds, the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic
21 Rising Scholars Award Program shall provide a scholarship in an
22 amount not to exceed the average costs of all enrollment fees,
23 tuition and other fees, room and board, and all required textbooks
24 or materials for up to five (5) years of undergraduate and/or
