23 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2404, is
24 amended to read as follows:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1282 Page 7
1 Section 2404. A. Scholarships awarded under the Oklahoma State
2 Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program shall be awarded to
3 all eligible applicants without any limitation on the number of
4 scholarships to be awarded in any year other than the amount of
5 funds available for the scholarship program and the number of
6 eligible applicants.
7 B. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may, at the
8 time a scholarship is awarded to a student, set aside in the
9 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Trust Fund
10 funds for the full five-year commitment made to such eligible
11 scholar. For all academic years, students who have previously
12 received academic scholarships under the provisions of this act and
13 who have continued at all times to fulfill the requirements for
14 eligibility to receive academic scholarships provided in this act
15 shall be given an absolute priority for continued financial support
16 by the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award
17 Program superior to any students who are applying for such academic
18 scholarships awards for the first time.
19 C. In addition to the qualifications specified in Section 2403
20 of this title, the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may
21 adopt additional criteria for selection and allocation of awards
22 which may include, but are not limited to, consideration of high
23 school academic performance and personal interviews. The Oklahoma
24 State Regents for Higher Education shall annually report on the
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1282 Page 8
1 numb er of former Academic Rising Scholars Award Program participants
2 who stay in state as compared to those who leave Oklahoma within
3 five (5) years of leaving the Award Program. In addition, the
4 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education are hereby authorized to
5 determine a maximum number of awards or a maximum amount of funding
6 which may go to nonresident students. Such maximum limitations
7 shall not exceed twenty-five percent (25%) of the awards or amount
8 of funding in any category provided in paragraph 2 of subsection A
9 of Section 2403 of this title.
10 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2405, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 2405. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
13 may adopt rules and regulations, prescribe and provide appropriate
14 forms for application, and employ such persons, contract for such
15 services and make such additional expenditures as may be necessary
16 or appropriate for implementing the provisions of the Oklahoma State
17 Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Act; provided, as part of
18 the regulations adopted for administration of the provisions of the
19 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program, the
20 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall require that each
21 scholarship recipient make continuing and satisfactory progress
22 toward a degree, including the establishment of an annual minimum
23 grade point average and annual minimum credit hours to be maintained
24 by the participants. Such regulations shall also provide for
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1282 Page 9
1 revo king or rescinding assistance to any scholarship recipient who
2 fails to meet such required standards. Such regulations shall also
3 provide that the funds made available to students as part of the
4 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program shall
5 be paid directly to the institution of the student's choice, in
6 trust for the student, and on the student's behalf, and shall
7 contain appropriate restrictions and conditions that such monies are
8 expended only for the purposes authorized by this act. Such
9 regulations shall also provide for portability of award for a
10 recipient among accredited institutions of higher education in
11 Oklahoma in which the recipient may enroll as long as the recipient
12 meets requirements of the program; however, waivers shall only be
13 portable between institutions in The Oklahoma State System of Higher
14 Education and waiver portability may be further limited by the
15 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education rules and regulations.
16 SECTION 6. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2406, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 2406. The Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising
19 Scholars Award Act shall not be construed as granting any authority
20 to control or influence the policies of any educational institution
21 because it accepts students who are participating in the scholarship
22 program, or to require any such institution to admit, or once
23 admitted to continue in such institution, any participant in the
24 scholarship program.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1282 Page 10
1 SECTION 7. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2407, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 2407. As part of its duties in administering the
4 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program, the
5 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, in cooperation with the
6 State Board of Education, shall encourage Oklahoma high school
7 juniors who plan to attend college to take the Preliminary
8 Scholastic Aptitude Test/National Merit Scholarship Qualifying Test
9 in their junior year in high school as preparation for taking the
10 Scholastic Aptitude Test their senior year in high school.
11 SECTION 8. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
